1
00:01:27,490 --> 00:01:31,940
[The Dark Romance]

2
00:01:32,150 --> 00:01:34,900
[Episode 5]

3
00:01:41,710 --> 00:01:47,270
[Guangzhong Road Exit]

4
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:43,729
Hello, Ms. Yan.

5
00:01:47,460 --> 00:01:52,710
[Good News]

6
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:54,370
[2019 Faculty Series
of Higher Education Institutions]

7
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:58,200
[Public Notice: Senior Professional Title
Successful Candidates]

8
00:02:01,150 --> 00:02:01,680
Yan Ling.

9
00:02:06,430 --> 00:02:08,560
I was looking through the list just now

10
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:10,280
and couldn't find your name.

11
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:11,710
This is so unfair.

12
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,190
I got a penalty,

13
00:02:14,470 --> 00:02:16,560
so my professional title review
didn't get approved.

14
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:17,820
It's understandable.

15
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:19,430
Besides, the university

16
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,310
has to give

17
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:23,170
an explanation to other faculty members.

18
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:25,460
You help others all day long,

19
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:26,360
and what's the result?

20
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,090
You ended up hurting yourself.

21
00:02:29,310 --> 00:02:30,570
It's not that serious.

22
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:31,560
You

23
00:02:31,390 --> 00:02:36,370
[Good News]

24
00:02:31,710 --> 00:02:33,510
just don't know the priorities.

25
00:02:34,030 --> 00:02:35,120
What if not getting
the senior professional title

26
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,780
affects your reappointment?

27
00:02:43,170 --> 00:02:44,910
[2019 Faculty Series
of Higher Education Institutions]

28
00:02:44,940 --> 00:02:47,140
[Public Notice: Senior Professional Title
Successful Candidates]

29
00:02:49,150 --> 00:02:50,240
I've verified
Xia Yi's passport information

30
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:52,840
with
the Entry-Exit Administration Department.

31
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,520
It's real.

32
00:02:56,630 --> 00:02:58,960
Who is the one
you asked me about last time,

33
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,560
the one at the beach?

34
00:03:04,630 --> 00:03:06,160
I will keep looking into it.

35
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:15,660
[Call History]

36
00:03:17,470 --> 00:03:18,120
Leilei,

37
00:03:19,430 --> 00:03:21,430
what exactly did you want to tell me?

38
00:03:22,710 --> 00:03:24,030
Just to say goodbye?

39
00:03:59,470 --> 00:04:00,470
Morning, Dr. Luo.

40
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,090
Morning.

41
00:04:01,910 --> 00:04:02,750
Have you had breakfast?

42
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:03,630
Yes. You?

43
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:04,360
Me too.

44
00:04:05,190 --> 00:04:05,520
Well,

45
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:07,190
there's an academic seminar next month.

46
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:08,850
[Incoming Call]

47
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:07,990
Are you going?

48
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,080
When is it?

49
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:10,500
The 18th of next month.

50
00:04:10,590 --> 00:04:12,150
I asked the nurse to put the invitation

51
00:04:12,150 --> 00:04:13,200
on your desk.

52
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:14,360
No problem.

53
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,120
I'll go up and take a look.

54
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:15,450
Okay.

55
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:19,820
[International Medical Center]

56
00:04:17,310 --> 00:04:18,070
Morning, Dr. Luo.

57
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:18,600
Morning.

58
00:04:19,630 --> 00:04:20,430
Hello, Dr. Luo.

59
00:04:19,870 --> 00:04:22,320
[Lihai Renxin Hospital]

60
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:20,920
Hello, Dr. Luo.

61
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:21,450
Morning.

62
00:04:22,950 --> 00:04:23,950
Morning, Dr. Luo.

63
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:24,770
Morning.

64
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:26,740
Fu,

65
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,810
give me some blank medical records.

66
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:29,360
Okay.

67
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:34,130
[Smile Service, Warm as Always]

68
00:04:39,409 --> 00:04:47,480
[Smile Service, Warm as Always]

69
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:52,750
Didn't I tell you

70
00:04:53,630 --> 00:04:54,960
not to call me casually?

71
00:05:26,010 --> 00:05:28,860
[Smile Service, Warm as Always]

72
00:05:59,120 --> 00:05:59,920
What's wrong?

73
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,390
Are you okay, Dr. Luo?

74
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:05,630
I'm fine.

75
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,460
I just bumped into something.

76
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,270
There aren't that many VIP patients.

77
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:11,480
No need to rush.

78
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:24,130
Let's grab dinner together
after work today.

79
00:06:27,430 --> 00:06:28,290
Did you forget?

80
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:30,760
I'm on the night shift today.
It's Tuesday.

81
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:31,560
How about...

82
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:31,870
Never mind.

83
00:06:31,870 --> 00:06:32,750
I'll ask Jiang to swap with...

84
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:34,150
That's too much trouble.

85
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:39,490
It's about time, right?

86
00:06:39,730 --> 00:06:40,860
Call the patient in.

87
00:06:58,390 --> 00:06:59,510
Sorry, I've really
never seen anything like this.

88
00:06:58,570 --> 00:07:03,030
[Lihai Tattoo Forum]

89
00:06:59,510 --> 00:07:00,830
Free design, free tattoo.

90
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:01,830
DM if interested.

91
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:03,430
I am a design major graduate,

92
00:07:03,510 --> 00:07:04,510
with solid basic skills,

93
00:07:04,510 --> 00:07:06,190
urgently seeking models
to build my tattoo portfolio.

94
00:07:06,190 --> 00:07:07,840
All posted works can be tattooed.

95
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:09,190
Completely free of charge.

96
00:07:09,190 --> 00:07:10,680
DM if interested.

97
00:07:11,820 --> 00:07:14,110
[Dr. Luo Liang]

98
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:18,020
Hello, Dr. Luo.

99
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:18,830
Ms. Yan.

100
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,430
Are you free tonight?

101
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:24,800
We didn't get together after you came back
from your hometown last time.

102
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,600
A restaurant just opened today.

103
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,600
Do you want to go try it together?

104
00:07:29,390 --> 00:07:31,500
Today is Tuesday.

105
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:33,190
You are going to reject me again?

106
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:33,800
No.

107
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,360
Okay.

108
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,400
I understand. I'm sorry.

109
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,420
I bothered you.

110
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:38,290
No, no, no.

111
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,690
You misunderstood.

112
00:07:41,950 --> 00:07:42,500
Okay.

113
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,950
Tonight is fine.

114
00:07:45,070 --> 00:07:45,600
Great.

115
00:07:46,190 --> 00:07:47,460
At 6:30 tonight.

116
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:49,560
I'll send you the address
of the restaurant.

117
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,140
Okay.

118
00:08:00,870 --> 00:08:01,400
Goodbye.

119
00:08:02,070 --> 00:08:02,600
Jiale.

120
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:11,730
Jiale, I will drop you off
at the programming class later.

121
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,850
Your dad will pick you up
when you are done.

122
00:08:13,850 --> 00:08:14,710
What about you?

123
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:17,250
I'm going to have dinner with Dr. Luo.

124
00:08:17,310 --> 00:08:18,360
Dr. Luo?

125
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,690
He's quite nice.

126
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:24,040
Mom.

127
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:26,660
I think you should wear

128
00:08:26,830 --> 00:08:29,510
the dress Godmother gave you.

129
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,440
It's still new.

130
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:33,480
I've never seen you wear it.

131
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:36,260
What's wrong with my clothes?

132
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:37,760
Isn't it good?

133
00:08:38,150 --> 00:08:39,880
You look like a female teacher.

134
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:43,320
I am a female teacher anyway.

135
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,600
Anyway, I think

136
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,800
you'll definitely look better in that.

137
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:02,970
You are here.

138
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:05,850
Give your bag to him.

139
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:08,580
Let me help you.

140
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:09,670
Thank you.

141
00:09:09,870 --> 00:09:10,800
Please sit down.

142
00:09:20,790 --> 00:09:22,000
Do you want to drink a little?

143
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:22,480
No.

144
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,830
I drove today.

145
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:24,930
Have a drink.

146
00:09:25,790 --> 00:09:26,970
I know you can drink.

147
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,550
You can call a designated driver
after drinking.

148
00:09:29,550 --> 00:09:30,880
Just to keep me company.

149
00:09:32,670 --> 00:09:33,330
Okay.

150
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,240
Are you okay?

151
00:09:59,000 --> 00:09:59,630
I'm fine.

152
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,760
It's just that suddenly,

153
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:05,300
I really wanted to see you.

154
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,890
I received a message today.

155
00:10:13,550 --> 00:10:14,810
My father passed away.

156
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:25,370
He had been disabled for so many years.

157
00:10:26,070 --> 00:10:27,240
For this day,

158
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:29,410
I had long been mentally prepared.

159
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,700
As a doctor,

160
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:35,990
I have seen so many partings and deaths.

161
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:40,030
But when it really happens to me,

162
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:42,910
I still...

163
00:10:49,910 --> 00:10:51,040
He was very serious.

164
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,720
I rarely saw him smile.

165
00:10:55,390 --> 00:10:56,850
He was also very talented,

166
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:59,720
but unfortunately born at the wrong time.

167
00:11:00,290 --> 00:11:01,520
He went from a student

168
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:03,080
to a farmer.

169
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:06,000
Axes and chainsaws

170
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:08,180
replaced his pens.

171
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:12,030
Later, a falling tree

172
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:13,720
broke his leg.

173
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:17,580
Get a car!

174
00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:19,050
Watch his legs!

175
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,250
The only time I saw him smile

176
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:31,300
was probably
when I got into medical school.

177
00:11:41,310 --> 00:11:42,370
Do you think...

178
00:11:45,070 --> 00:11:46,670
I look vulnerable like this?

179
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:49,960
No.

180
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:50,960
No.

181
00:11:56,170 --> 00:11:57,830
Actually, in our line of work,

182
00:11:59,180 --> 00:11:59,980
it's very sad.

183
00:12:03,030 --> 00:12:04,000
We constantly

184
00:12:04,550 --> 00:12:07,150
deal with other people's
emotional problems,

185
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:09,820
but it's hard for us...

186
00:12:13,270 --> 00:12:14,960
to get comfort from others.

187
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:19,720
Thank you for trusting me

188
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,490
and telling me this.

189
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:25,320
I understand.

190
00:12:26,630 --> 00:12:27,760
I know what you mean.

191
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:29,870
I understand.

192
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:32,970
The moment I got the news today,

193
00:12:35,870 --> 00:12:37,320
I just wanted to call you.

194
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:50,360
Excuse me.

195
00:12:53,870 --> 00:12:54,800
Enjoy your meal.

196
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:57,780
You should eat something too.

197
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,520
I asked you out for dinner

198
00:12:59,540 --> 00:13:01,400
and told you so many sad things,

199
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:02,750
ruining your appetite.

200
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,840
It makes me feel very guilty.

201
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:25,640
What's wrong?

202
00:13:34,270 --> 00:13:36,000
My father passed away too.

203
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:42,130
When I was 14.

204
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:05,390
They say

205
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:07,880
if you share your sorrow,

206
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:10,240
it's reduced by half.

207
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,750
Thank you

208
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,200
for keeping me company tonight.

209
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:19,770
My condolences.

210
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:20,840
Take care.

211
00:14:22,460 --> 00:14:24,030
If you ever feel sad—

212
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,120
I'll call you.

213
00:14:33,630 --> 00:14:35,230
Let me know when you get home.

214
00:14:53,050 --> 00:14:54,730
[Wuzhou City]

215
00:15:52,180 --> 00:15:55,050
[Dismantle]

216
00:15:55,980 --> 00:15:57,530
[Dismantle]

217
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:23,490
Get lost!

218
00:17:30,510 --> 00:17:31,350
Pick it up.

219
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:35,210
Are you deaf?

220
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,000
You're back.

221
00:17:51,050 --> 00:17:52,850
You didn't even tell me earlier.

222
00:17:57,590 --> 00:17:58,530
Have you eaten?

223
00:17:59,790 --> 00:18:00,440
Not yet.

224
00:18:01,550 --> 00:18:02,160
And you?

225
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,330
I brought some back.

226
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:07,060
You're eating someone else's
leftovers again.

227
00:18:09,310 --> 00:18:10,420
It's untouched.

228
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:13,640
Don't I send money back every month?

229
00:18:14,270 --> 00:18:16,070
Why do you have to live like this?

230
00:18:19,350 --> 00:18:20,070
He's dead.

231
00:18:21,830 --> 00:18:22,680
Are you happy?

232
00:18:33,550 --> 00:18:34,750
He got off too easily.

233
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:43,960
Here,

234
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:45,640
eat it while it's hot.

235
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:47,660
You eat too.

236
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:49,240
Eat.

237
00:19:12,430 --> 00:19:13,040
Eat.

238
00:19:20,590 --> 00:19:21,690
The funeral

239
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:23,520
will cost money too.

240
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:24,440
I know.

241
00:19:27,210 --> 00:19:27,920
And...

242
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:31,990
your sister...

243
00:19:32,270 --> 00:19:33,400
Why bring her up?

244
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:41,550
If she hears the news,

245
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,730
she will definitely come home.

246
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:50,200
I'll arrange the cremation tomorrow.

247
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:52,260
Forget about the farewell ceremony.

248
00:19:52,350 --> 00:19:54,410
I'll also hurry up with the cemetery.

249
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:56,510
Okay.

250
00:19:58,720 --> 00:19:59,200
Okay.

251
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:16,030
You are just a little brat!

252
00:20:16,070 --> 00:20:16,880
Day after day,

253
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:18,360
all you do is drag me down!

254
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:19,660
And you,

255
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:21,900
just like your mom,

256
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:22,960
shameless!

257
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:23,750
My whole life

258
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,910
has been ruined by you two!

259
00:20:26,110 --> 00:20:27,650
If it weren't for you two,

260
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,440
I would have returned
to the city long ago.

261
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:31,700
It's all your fault!

262
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:34,400
You're always trying to seduce me!

263
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,200
I will beat you to death today!

264
00:20:36,310 --> 00:20:36,880
Get lost!

265
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:37,800
Get lost!

266
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:39,510
Don't let me see you again!

267
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:54,280
Hello,

268
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:54,920
Mom.

269
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:56,960
How is your work lately?

270
00:20:58,920 --> 00:20:59,880
Pretty good.

271
00:21:00,590 --> 00:21:02,720
You've been a lecturer for 4 or 5 years.

272
00:21:02,790 --> 00:21:04,960
Should you get promoted
to associate professor?

273
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:06,290
Did you apply this year?

274
00:21:07,830 --> 00:21:09,560
It'll be a while longer.

275
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:10,960
Keep lying.

276
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:13,000
You never tell me the truth.

277
00:21:13,030 --> 00:21:15,160
I've looked through the public list

278
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:16,160
on your university's website.

279
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:17,420
You're not on it at all.

280
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:19,070
Universities nowadays have

281
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:20,750
the "up or out" policy.

282
00:21:21,110 --> 00:21:22,710
What are you going to do next?

283
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:24,110
If you don't get promoted this year,

284
00:21:24,110 --> 00:21:25,640
you'll be fired.

285
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:29,070
It's not that serious.

286
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:32,230
Our university doesn't have that rule.

287
00:21:32,430 --> 00:21:33,720
You're no longer on your own,

288
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:34,640
with no one else to feed.

289
00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:35,840
You still have Jiale.

290
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,630
When you got pregnant,
you insisted on having him,

291
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:39,070
claiming you could raise him.

292
00:21:39,070 --> 00:21:39,640
And now?

293
00:21:40,110 --> 00:21:40,640
How are you going to raise him?

294
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:42,480
You just do whatever you want,

295
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:43,400
just like when you were little.

296
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:44,350
You only think about yourself.

297
00:21:44,350 --> 00:21:45,880
You never consider others.

298
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:46,780
Let me tell you,

299
00:21:46,860 --> 00:21:47,790
this isn't over.

300
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:49,860
Think carefully about what to do.

301
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:13,910
[Dr. Luo Liang]

302
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:15,610
[Are you busy?]

303
00:22:15,630 --> 00:22:18,110
[It's okay. Call me when you're done.]

304
00:22:18,130 --> 00:22:19,850
[No hurry.]

305
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,120
[Yan Ling]

306
00:22:51,270 --> 00:22:51,790
Hello.

307
00:22:53,110 --> 00:22:53,590
Hello.

308
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:55,930
Are you okay?

309
00:22:57,350 --> 00:22:58,500
I was just worried

310
00:22:59,110 --> 00:23:01,840
that I brought up
some sad memories the other day.

311
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:03,260
I'm sorry.

312
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:06,510
No, I'm fine.

313
00:23:08,110 --> 00:23:08,970
What about you?

314
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:12,110
Did everything go smoothly
after you went back?

315
00:23:12,110 --> 00:23:12,770
It was okay.

316
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:16,440
I arranged the cremation for tomorrow.

317
00:23:16,830 --> 00:23:17,960
But my mom...

318
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:21,400
has been vomiting and having diarrhea.

319
00:23:22,110 --> 00:23:23,570
I took her to the hospital,

320
00:23:24,350 --> 00:23:25,750
and she just stabilized.

321
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:28,240
Is your mom okay?

322
00:23:29,070 --> 00:23:31,350
She's actually always been in good health.

323
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:33,030
It's probably a physical reaction

324
00:23:33,030 --> 00:23:34,440
caused by her emotions.

325
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:38,110
The other day,

326
00:23:39,640 --> 00:23:41,350
you suddenly felt sick and threw up.

327
00:23:41,350 --> 00:23:43,350
You must have been very sad too.

328
00:23:47,030 --> 00:23:48,480
Could you please teach me

329
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:51,830
how to get through this?

330
00:23:54,750 --> 00:23:56,810
I might not be qualified to teach you.

331
00:24:12,310 --> 00:24:13,660
I would recall...

332
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,930
By holding onto the best memories,

333
00:24:20,130 --> 00:24:21,270
in my heart,

334
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,800
it seems as if he were still here.

335
00:24:34,860 --> 00:24:36,510
Uncle, is there a letter for me today?

336
00:24:36,510 --> 00:24:37,140
Yes.

337
00:24:37,540 --> 00:24:39,680
[For my beloved Ling]

338
00:24:38,110 --> 00:24:39,320
I would repeatedly

339
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:41,490
read the letters he wrote to me.

340
00:24:43,270 --> 00:24:43,960
My dad

341
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:47,860
would talk to me about the sea.

342
00:24:49,940 --> 00:24:51,140
He told me

343
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:54,000
smearing engine oil on your face

344
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:55,240
can prevent sunburn

345
00:24:56,790 --> 00:24:58,720
and that if there's no fresh water,

346
00:24:59,110 --> 00:25:00,770
eating fish can replenish it.

347
00:25:01,750 --> 00:25:02,910
He would teach me

348
00:25:03,310 --> 00:25:04,910
how to identify directions.

349
00:25:06,790 --> 00:25:07,970
Dad said

350
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:11,600
point the hour hand of your watch
at the sun,

351
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:14,590
and the bisector of the acute angle

352
00:25:14,590 --> 00:25:17,320
between the hour hand
and the 12 o'clock position

353
00:25:17,830 --> 00:25:18,880
points south.

354
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:23,110
Come on, hold on, baby.

355
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:25,200
Dad would teach me

356
00:25:26,750 --> 00:25:28,340
how to avoid storms.

357
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:30,320
Be brave,

358
00:25:30,550 --> 00:25:33,010
and even the biggest storm
can be conquered.

359
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:35,030
He said no matter how big

360
00:25:35,830 --> 00:25:37,290
or dangerous the storm is,

361
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:39,080
you must never give up

362
00:25:41,030 --> 00:25:42,590
or let go of the helm.

363
00:25:44,550 --> 00:25:45,680
He really was

364
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:48,680
a great father.

365
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:51,790
Did he work at sea?

366
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:56,460
He was the captain of an ocean freighter.

367
00:25:57,880 --> 00:25:58,930
So he

368
00:26:00,640 --> 00:26:01,970
died in the line of duty?

369
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:04,880
No.

370
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:09,500
During a family visit,

371
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,220
he had an accident.

372
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:23,170
I originally thought

373
00:26:24,310 --> 00:26:26,310
I could recover and move on quickly.

374
00:26:28,550 --> 00:26:29,550
But it doesn't feel

375
00:26:29,550 --> 00:26:30,490
realistic.

376
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:32,540
Look at you,

377
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:35,680
it's been so long,

378
00:26:36,750 --> 00:26:38,610
and it seems you haven't moved on.

379
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:43,820
I'm so sorry.

380
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:47,400
I was supposed to comfort you,

381
00:26:48,510 --> 00:26:50,510
but I ended up doing all the talking.

382
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:53,560
Not at all.

383
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:55,810
Thank you so much

384
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:58,800
for sharing all this with me.

385
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:04,240
Getting through it
by holding onto good memories.

386
00:27:06,350 --> 00:27:07,880
I've learned how to do that.

387
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:10,880
You know what?

388
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:14,510
Before this,

389
00:27:17,270 --> 00:27:19,670
I've never told anyone about these things.

390
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:24,010
Then you must have been a kid

391
00:27:24,510 --> 00:27:26,640
who was very sensible from a young age.

392
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:29,240
With such deep sorrow in your heart,

393
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:31,540
you didn't share it with your mom.

394
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,590
You must have been very afraid

395
00:27:33,590 --> 00:27:35,650
of breaking your mom's heart, right?

396
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:39,390
You and your mother

397
00:27:40,590 --> 00:27:42,790
have depended on each other all the way.

398
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:44,900
It must have been really hard.

399
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:50,720
Dad.

400
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:04,680
Hello?

401
00:28:07,390 --> 00:28:08,520
Are you still there?

402
00:28:13,270 --> 00:28:13,960
Yes.

403
00:28:16,190 --> 00:28:17,330
I'm sorry.

404
00:28:18,070 --> 00:28:18,510
I...

405
00:28:18,510 --> 00:28:19,590
I just got

406
00:28:19,590 --> 00:28:20,440
a work WeChat message.

407
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:21,840
I have to get back to work.

408
00:28:24,030 --> 00:28:24,590
Sure.

409
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:27,130
I should be the one apologizing

410
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:29,330
for taking up your time.

411
00:28:30,310 --> 00:28:31,120
No, not at all.

412
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:34,170
Take good care of your mom

413
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:35,800
and yourself.

414
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:38,090
I will.

415
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:40,690
You too.

416
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:42,160
Goodbye.

417
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:53,330
Family members.

418
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:56,010
Let me.

419
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:58,850
My condolences.

420
00:30:09,030 --> 00:30:09,720
I'll call you a car.

421
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:10,720
You go back first.

422
00:30:11,030 --> 00:30:11,890
What about you?

423
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:16,710
I'll go find a better box,

424
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:18,550
then go to the cemetery in advance

425
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:19,810
to make arrangements.

426
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:35,450
Hello.

427
00:30:35,510 --> 00:30:36,910
Feel free to look around.

428
00:30:45,830 --> 00:30:47,140
Let me see that box.

429
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:48,110
Sure.

430
00:30:53,110 --> 00:30:54,720
This one is made of red sandalwood.

431
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:55,980
It's quite expensive.

432
00:31:01,510 --> 00:31:02,240
I'll take it.

433
00:31:02,590 --> 00:31:03,000
Sure.

434
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:15,280
What are your best scissors?

435
00:31:16,230 --> 00:31:16,740
Sir,

436
00:31:17,070 --> 00:31:18,400
take a look at this pair.

437
00:31:18,550 --> 00:31:19,070
This pair

438
00:31:19,070 --> 00:31:20,730
is an original German Jaguar.

439
00:31:21,510 --> 00:31:23,840
It's the most professional and high-end.

440
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:26,370
We also have Kasho and Sassoon.

441
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:28,050
Kasho is also very good.

442
00:31:28,350 --> 00:31:30,210
We have their Millennium Series.

443
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:55,300
Don't move around.

444
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:57,350
Be careful not to get your ears cut.

445
00:31:57,350 --> 00:31:58,960
You are the smartest in the family.

446
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:00,090
You must study hard.

447
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:02,680
I am really studying hard.

448
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:04,260
Really.

449
00:32:05,790 --> 00:32:07,540
I knew you had it in you.

450
00:32:07,790 --> 00:32:08,840
In my life,

451
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:10,310
I can only do haircuts for others.

452
00:32:10,310 --> 00:32:11,370
You are different.

453
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,440
You are going to get a PhD,

454
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:13,070
become a doctor,

455
00:32:13,070 --> 00:32:14,240
and hold a scalpel.

456
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:16,640
You've been good with your hands
since you were little.

457
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:19,160
You must go to the best university
in the future.

458
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:20,200
You'll go to Shenchuan

459
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:21,130
or Gangdao.

460
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:22,600
I will earn your tuition.

461
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:43,880
Dr. Luo

462
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:45,070
sent me

463
00:32:45,070 --> 00:32:46,070
a WeChat message.

464
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:47,270
Did he?

465
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:49,580
What did he say?

466
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:53,200
He said to thank me
for helping him take care of the hamster

467
00:32:53,200 --> 00:32:55,240
and let you add a chicken leg
to my dinner.

468
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:57,370
He'll reimburse you when he gets back.

469
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,000
Okay,

470
00:32:59,510 --> 00:33:00,170
no problem.

471
00:33:03,870 --> 00:33:04,400
Alright.

472
00:33:05,070 --> 00:33:05,670
Let me see.

473
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:08,360
Get up

474
00:33:08,440 --> 00:33:09,700
and look in the mirror.

475
00:33:11,070 --> 00:33:11,730
Take a look.

476
00:33:12,550 --> 00:33:13,350
Do you like it?

477
00:33:14,790 --> 00:33:15,790
It's pretty good.

478
00:33:16,500 --> 00:33:18,160
You've never asked me before

479
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:19,000
if I liked it.

480
00:33:20,790 --> 00:33:21,500
Really?

481
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:25,290
Then I'll ask more often in the future.

482
00:33:26,440 --> 00:33:27,770
Shall we take a picture?

483
00:33:28,510 --> 00:33:28,970
Come on.

484
00:33:32,330 --> 00:33:33,140
Smile.

485
00:33:34,920 --> 00:33:35,510
Alright.

486
00:33:39,830 --> 00:33:40,890
Is it Dr. Luo?

487
00:33:41,350 --> 00:33:41,750
No.

488
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:43,890
Hello, who is it?

489
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:05,260
What's wrong with you?

490
00:34:05,590 --> 00:34:06,550
What happened?

491
00:34:09,159 --> 00:34:09,560
Hurry.

492
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:11,090
Get in the car first.

493
00:34:20,719 --> 00:34:22,179
He knew you were pregnant

494
00:34:22,199 --> 00:34:23,929
and still beat you up like this?

495
00:34:25,280 --> 00:34:27,679
How can you forgive him
time and time again?

496
00:34:28,190 --> 00:34:30,850
He's been under a lot of pressure
at work lately.

497
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:33,850
Don't make excuses for him.

498
00:34:34,150 --> 00:34:36,030
Even if you don't think about yourself,

499
00:34:36,030 --> 00:34:37,960
think about the baby in your belly.

500
00:34:46,030 --> 00:34:47,810
How did you get this tattoo?

501
00:34:48,280 --> 00:34:49,340
Who made you get it?

502
00:34:49,670 --> 00:34:51,400
Was it your husband? Was it him?

503
00:34:53,510 --> 00:34:54,340
It wasn't him.

504
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:57,360
It has nothing to do with him.

505
00:34:57,510 --> 00:34:59,000
It's all my fault.

506
00:34:59,800 --> 00:35:01,150
I'm a very bad person.

507
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:03,500
I deserved to be beaten by him.

508
00:35:09,670 --> 00:35:10,700
Before...

509
00:35:12,630 --> 00:35:13,890
I borrowed some money.

510
00:35:15,250 --> 00:35:17,850
But I didn't know
the interest would be so high.

511
00:35:18,670 --> 00:35:19,920
The debt snowballed.

512
00:35:20,760 --> 00:35:22,020
I couldn't pay it back.

513
00:35:23,510 --> 00:35:24,760
So I was forced by the creditors

514
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:27,540
to get this tattoo as they demanded.

515
00:35:28,590 --> 00:35:30,440
I also took those kinds of photos.

516
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:33,240
They said taking them
would offset some interest.

517
00:35:33,960 --> 00:35:34,470
You mean

518
00:35:35,190 --> 00:35:35,970
Leilei

519
00:35:36,960 --> 00:35:38,160
took out a naked loan?

520
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:39,550
So I guess

521
00:35:40,440 --> 00:35:42,050
the tattoo on Leilei

522
00:35:42,670 --> 00:35:43,440
was also done according to

523
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:45,040
the demands of these people.

524
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:50,170
How much did you borrow?

525
00:35:51,550 --> 00:35:53,010
The principal was 80,000.

526
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:55,270
Then I don't know what happened.

527
00:35:55,510 --> 00:35:57,310
The interest just kept rolling,

528
00:35:57,760 --> 00:35:59,710
and it ended up
being hundreds of thousands.

529
00:35:59,710 --> 00:36:01,040
What about your family?

530
00:36:01,630 --> 00:36:02,830
Didn't they help you?

531
00:36:06,030 --> 00:36:08,760
I wasn't in touch with my family
during that time.

532
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:11,540
My father passed away.

533
00:36:13,290 --> 00:36:14,220
Because of me.

534
00:36:16,070 --> 00:36:16,710
At that time,

535
00:36:16,710 --> 00:36:18,710
I was supposed to be home with my dad,

536
00:36:19,190 --> 00:36:20,920
but I had a fight
with my boyfriend and broke up,

537
00:36:20,920 --> 00:36:22,130
so I ran out.

538
00:36:27,150 --> 00:36:28,670
Then he had a heart attack,

539
00:36:28,670 --> 00:36:29,670
and I wasn't home.

540
00:36:31,670 --> 00:36:32,930
It's all because of me.

541
00:36:34,030 --> 00:36:35,420
I was young

542
00:36:35,630 --> 00:36:36,840
and very ignorant.

543
00:36:37,140 --> 00:36:38,590
If it wasn't for me,

544
00:36:38,710 --> 00:36:40,240
my father wouldn't have...

545
00:36:45,290 --> 00:36:46,160
After that,

546
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:50,210
my relationship with my mom also went bad.

547
00:36:51,510 --> 00:36:52,710
I knew she blamed me.

548
00:36:55,220 --> 00:36:57,350
And I couldn't forgive myself either.

549
00:36:57,980 --> 00:36:59,540
So I moved out of the house.

550
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:02,980
Later, my mom was very sad

551
00:37:03,090 --> 00:37:04,420
and immigrated abroad.

552
00:37:05,130 --> 00:37:06,190
Thinking back now,

553
00:37:06,190 --> 00:37:08,070
those years were a living hell.

554
00:37:08,070 --> 00:37:09,590
I did a lot of wrong things,

555
00:37:10,670 --> 00:37:12,270
including borrowing money.

556
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:17,470
Later on,

557
00:37:19,190 --> 00:37:20,480
I met Liu Ping.

558
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:24,010
He treated me really, really well.

559
00:37:25,190 --> 00:37:27,520
So I didn't want
to hide anything from him.

560
00:37:28,130 --> 00:37:29,650
After I told him,

561
00:37:31,500 --> 00:37:33,160
he said his heart ached for me,

562
00:37:34,900 --> 00:37:37,540
and then he went and got
the same tattoo as mine.

563
00:37:39,670 --> 00:37:41,670
He said that by getting this tattoo,

564
00:37:41,670 --> 00:37:42,840
it would no longer be

565
00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:44,670
a painful and shameful memory.

566
00:37:45,590 --> 00:37:47,840
It would be a testament to our love.

567
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:49,660
But...

568
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:53,150
accepting the way I used to be

569
00:37:53,150 --> 00:37:54,550
might have been too hard.

570
00:37:55,030 --> 00:37:56,700
Every time he got drunk,

571
00:37:57,030 --> 00:37:58,760
he couldn't help but curse at me

572
00:37:58,840 --> 00:37:59,550
and beat me.

573
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:03,490
I don't blame him at all.

574
00:38:03,490 --> 00:38:04,840
I only blame myself.

575
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:06,650
I really regret it.

576
00:38:06,710 --> 00:38:07,710
I wish I had never done

577
00:38:07,710 --> 00:38:09,630
those shameful things.

578
00:38:09,630 --> 00:38:12,590
I don't want anyone
to know about these things.

579
00:38:17,510 --> 00:38:18,400
I remember

580
00:38:19,070 --> 00:38:21,110
what you told me about your friend

581
00:38:21,630 --> 00:38:22,550
and her tattoo.

582
00:38:24,650 --> 00:38:26,780
I think she must have regretted it too.

583
00:38:28,010 --> 00:38:30,670
Otherwise,
she wouldn't have made that choice.

584
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:36,700
Ling.

585
00:38:39,830 --> 00:38:41,570
Will you look down on us?

586
00:38:42,650 --> 00:38:45,050
No, of course not.

587
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:50,060
So what's next?

588
00:38:50,730 --> 00:38:51,950
Do you have any plans?

589
00:38:57,320 --> 00:38:58,620
If possible,

590
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:02,340
could you lend me some money?

591
00:39:03,100 --> 00:39:05,900
I want to buy a plane ticket
and hide out for a while.

592
00:39:06,740 --> 00:39:08,990
Because I gave all my money to him.

593
00:39:14,540 --> 00:39:16,510
[Jianan Rd.(S)] [Xingxing Rd]

594
00:39:26,230 --> 00:39:28,140
The friend you mentioned,

595
00:39:28,800 --> 00:39:30,930
I think she must have regretted it too.

596
00:39:31,510 --> 00:39:32,800
She might have been even more regretful

597
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:34,200
and in more pain than I am.

598
00:39:34,230 --> 00:39:36,790
Otherwise,
she wouldn't have made that choice.

599
00:39:36,790 --> 00:39:38,900
I've made a terrible mistake

600
00:39:39,110 --> 00:39:40,710
that I can't make up for in this lifetime.

601
00:39:40,710 --> 00:39:43,280
I owe you too much.

602
00:39:43,550 --> 00:39:45,280
I will repay you in my next life.

603
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:47,760
Because you think Godmother
was a bad person

604
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:49,890
whose mistakes couldn't be forgiven.

605
00:39:50,750 --> 00:39:52,700
Will you look down on us?

606
00:39:52,770 --> 00:39:53,950
[Jianan Rd.(S)] [Xingxing Rd]

607
00:40:04,020 --> 00:40:05,350
I don't blame him at all.

608
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:06,780
I only blame myself.

609
00:40:06,840 --> 00:40:08,400
I really regret it.

610
00:40:08,590 --> 00:40:09,510
I wish I had never done

611
00:40:09,510 --> 00:40:11,480
those shameful things.

612
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:14,400
I don't want anyone
to know about these things.

613
00:40:14,790 --> 00:40:17,360
Why did I miss your call?

614
00:40:17,100 --> 00:40:19,010
[Call History]

615
00:40:18,070 --> 00:40:20,330
Why did I fail to save you?

616
00:40:30,160 --> 00:40:32,460
[I am Yan Ling.]

617
00:40:35,130 --> 00:40:35,440
[Yan Ling]

618
00:40:35,560 --> 00:40:38,200
[Sometimes kids' happiness
is really simple.]

619
00:40:39,670 --> 00:40:40,590
A little bit...

620
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:43,640
A little bit higher.

621
00:40:51,710 --> 00:40:52,440
Ling.

622
00:40:52,670 --> 00:40:53,280
Kexin.

623
00:40:55,070 --> 00:40:56,370
I'll ask you again.

624
00:40:56,910 --> 00:40:58,780
Are you really going to,
because of that past,

625
00:40:58,780 --> 00:41:01,040
let him beat you
for the rest of your life?

626
00:41:05,360 --> 00:41:06,440
I'm not afraid.

627
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:08,110
But I am afraid

628
00:41:08,110 --> 00:41:10,110
that my child will be beaten like me.

629
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:14,340
Have you ever thought about changing

630
00:41:14,480 --> 00:41:15,540
and starting over?

631
00:41:17,480 --> 00:41:18,590
You mean

632
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:20,690
divorce?

633
00:41:22,040 --> 00:41:23,370
I have thought about it.

634
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:25,320
I have.

635
00:41:26,630 --> 00:41:28,480
Because I don't want my child to grow up

636
00:41:28,480 --> 00:41:30,770
living in fear every day like me.

637
00:41:30,790 --> 00:41:33,480
If you make a mistake,
you should cut your losses in time.

638
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:36,010
You can't make up for it
with another mistake.

639
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:38,560
That will only make things worse

640
00:41:39,400 --> 00:41:41,200
and ultimately irretrievable.

641
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:51,900
My good friend

642
00:41:53,400 --> 00:41:56,000
had no one to help her
during her hardest times,

643
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:58,960
so she could only make
one mistake after another.

644
00:41:58,960 --> 00:41:59,690
In the end,

645
00:42:00,110 --> 00:42:03,240
she didn't even have the chance
to regret and start over.

646
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:08,310
Let's not do anything

647
00:42:09,880 --> 00:42:11,400
that we will regret,

648
00:42:12,480 --> 00:42:13,150
okay?

649
00:42:20,480 --> 00:42:21,710
Then what should I do?

650
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:25,370
I'll help you find a lawyer.

651
00:42:26,510 --> 00:42:27,590
I'm worried

652
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:30,260
that you won't be able to handle it alone.

653
00:42:30,360 --> 00:42:31,960
You need someone to help you.

654
00:42:35,480 --> 00:42:36,190
Thank you.

655
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:41,360
I really don't know how to thank you.

656
00:42:45,550 --> 00:42:47,440
I wish we had met earlier.

657
00:42:49,590 --> 00:42:51,450
Let's not talk about this for now.

658
00:42:52,070 --> 00:42:54,150
The most important thing for you right now

659
00:42:54,150 --> 00:42:55,610
is to take care of your body

660
00:42:55,710 --> 00:42:57,440
and keep your emotions stable.

661
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:00,060
After all, you are eating for two now.

662
00:43:04,030 --> 00:43:05,790
I can raise you by myself,

663
00:43:06,030 --> 00:43:06,550
right?

664
00:43:11,960 --> 00:43:12,630
Thank you.

665
00:43:13,760 --> 00:43:14,550
Thank you.

666
00:43:17,720 --> 00:43:18,400
Don't cry.

667
00:43:19,670 --> 00:43:20,530
It will be okay.

668
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:22,960
Everything will get better.

669
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:29,740
[The Dark Romance]

670
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:35,340
Ma'am,

671
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:36,990
do you need help?

672
00:43:37,190 --> 00:43:39,000
Grab whatever you want for yourself.

673
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:40,860
-Thank you. No need.
-Okay, okay.

674
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:43,960
Changning, you go watch the shop.

675
00:43:44,030 --> 00:43:45,160
I will be right back.

676
00:43:45,190 --> 00:43:45,670
Okay.

677
00:43:54,780 --> 00:43:57,710
[Video 1]

678
00:44:00,270 --> 00:44:01,090
[Daily Necessities, Tobacco,
Wine & Groceries]

679
00:44:14,230 --> 00:44:14,760
Ma'am,

680
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:16,460
how much are these?

681
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:21,280
[A Leaf of Loneliness]

682
00:44:19,590 --> 00:44:20,400
Are you okay?

683
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:22,490
I miss you very much.

684
00:44:22,550 --> 00:44:23,000
Ma'am.

685
00:44:23,770 --> 00:44:24,640
[A Leaf of Loneliness]

686
00:44:24,760 --> 00:44:25,360
Ma'am!

687
00:44:26,400 --> 00:44:27,400
How much are these?
